IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE QUALITY, PATIENT-CENTERED PRIMARY HEALTH CARE, DENTAL AND OTHER SERVICES TO THE MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED IN UTAH REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE QUALITY, PATIENT-CENTERED PRIMARY HEALTH CARE, DENTAL AND OTHER SERVICES TO THE MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED IN UTAH REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY.
IRS990.Desc: COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS PROVIDED PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE TO 42,926 PATIENTS WITH 109,956 INDIVIDUAL VISITS, ORAL HEALTH CARE TO 2,457 PATIENTS WITH 9,188 INDIVIDUAL VISITS AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE TO 1,266 PATIENTS WITH 3,328 INDIVIDUAL VISITS. THESE SERVICES ARE PROVIDED THROUGH DIRECT SERVICE HEALTH CLINICS TO LOW INCOME AND MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATIONS THROUGHOUT THE STATE OF UTAH. PRIMARY MEDICAL CARE INCLUDES A SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON PEDIATRIC MEDICINE, WITH 17,658 WELL CHILD CHECKUPS AND 31,667 VACCINES GIVEN TO CHILDREN UNDER AGE 18. CHC ALSO PROVIDED ORAL HEALTH CARE EDUCATION, OUTREACH AND TREATMENTS TO CHILDREN OF MIGRANT FARMWORKERS IN UTAH COUNTY THROUGH A PARTNER ORGANIZATION, COMMUNITY HEALTH CONNECT. THIS PROGRAM BENEFITED 5,132 CHILDREN IN 2021.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND, AS REQUIRED, FILES A FORM 990 (RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX) ANNUALLY. THE ORGANIZATION ENGAGES IN NO ACTIVITY CONSTITUTING TAXABLE UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. CONSEQUENTLY, THE ORGANIZATION IS NOT SUBJECT TO FEDERAL OR STATE INCOME TAXES ON INCOME PERTAINING TO ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE AND NO INCOME TAX IS REFLECTED IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ORGANIZATION HAS NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE EITHER RECOGNITION OR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
REPORTED THE NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTIONS FOR DRUGS AND MEDICAL SUPPLIES, AND THE NUMBER OF DONATED VACCINES.

TAXPAYER IS AMENDING THE RETURN TO REPORT PART VII INFORMATION INADVERTENTLY OMITTED ON THE ORIGINAL FILING AND TO CORRECT ANY RELATED SECTIONS OF THE RETURN, INCLUDING PART IX, STATEMENT OF FUNCTIONAL EXPENSES.

THE FINANCE DIRECTOR COMPARES THE FORM 990 TO THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND REVIEWS THE VARIOUS OTHER DISCLOSURES WITH THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR. A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS ALSO PRESENTED BY EMAIL, DISCUSSED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF GOVERNORS.

HUMAN RESOURCES REQUIRES ALL NEW EMPLOYEES AND BOARD MEMBERS TO COMPLETE AND SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT. OUR COMPLIANCE OFFICER REVIEWS ALL CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS AND INVESTIGATES ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS. BOARD MEMBERS DO NOT VOTE ON ISSUES FOR WHICH THEY MAY HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST.

HUMAN RESOURCES CONDUCTS A COMPENSATION STUDY AND MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS TO A COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD CHARGED WITH EVALUATING THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S JOB PERFORMANCE. THE COMMITTEE THEN APPROVES THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S COMPENSATION AND RENEWAL OF EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT.

FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, AND COMPANY POLICIES CAN BE OBTAINED BY CONTACTING JENNIFER THOMAS EITHER BY PHONE AT 801-412-6920 OR BY MAIL AT 2621 SOUTH 3270 WEST, WEST VALLEY CITY, UT 84119.
